In[20]:
virsorter_contigs = set(vs_viral["contig_id"])
virsorter2_contigs = set(vs2_viral["contig_id"])
dvf_contigs = set(dvf_viral["contig_id"])

layout_algorithm=DefaultLayoutAlgorithm(fixed_subset_sizes=sizes_adapted) - needed for troubleshooting of missing values on a plot

In[21]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
sizes = (538, 13405, 4595, 2949, 102, 6679, 2430) ## hardcoded for troubleshooting
mean_size = sum(sizes)/len(sizes)
sizes_adapted = [s + 0.1*mean_size for s in sizes]
venn3([virsorter_contigs, virsorter2_contigs, dvf_contigs], ('VirSorter', 'VirSorter2', 'DeepVirFinder'), set_colors=("#0173b2", "#de8f05", "#029e73" ), alpha=0.6, layout_algorithm=DefaultLayoutAlgorithm(fixed_subset_sizes=sizes_adapted))
venn3_circles(subsets=(virsorter_contigs, virsorter2_contigs,dvf_contigs), linewidth=0.5, layout_algorithm=DefaultLayoutAlgorithm(fixed_subset_sizes=sizes_adapted))  
plt.title('Venn`s Diagram of overlapping CheckV identified True Positive results',  size = 20, pad=30)
plt.show()
